        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 6:46PM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 646 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Hendley to 9 miles northwest of Norton.
Movement was east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Hendley around 650 PM CDT.
Beaver City around 700 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of these storms include Hollinger.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
